## When filtering which modules are syncable

Use `setModuleFilter` to restrict which DB modules participate in smart-sync (e.g. based on user permissions):

```typescript
ModuleBE_SyncManager.setModuleFilter(async (modules) => {
	return modules.filter(m => isUserAllowedToSync(m.dbDef.dbKey));
});
```

Filters are composable â€” each call wraps the previous filter.

---

## When overriding the RTDB path

Default path is `/state/ModuleBE_SyncManager`. Override with:

```typescript
ModuleBE_SyncManager.setResolvablePath(() => `/custom/sync/path`);
```

---

## RTDB state shape (for debugging)

```
/state/ModuleBE_SyncManager/
  syncData/
    {dbKey}/
      lastUpdated: number     // max __updated across all items in collection
  deletedCount: number        // total deleted-doc records (for cleanup)
```

---

## Deleted documents

When items are deleted, the sync manager stores them in a `deleted-docs` Firestore collection. On `DeltaSync`, deleted items since the requested timestamp are included in the response so the frontend can remove them from IDB.

Config for cleanup retention:

```json
{
  "ModuleBE_SyncManager": {
    "retainDeletedCount": 1000
  }
}
```

